Description:
This document describes an example of how to use health2api directory to browse information
and create mashup based on search results.

Pre-requisites:

Hpricot

It can be installed quite easily:
$: gem install hpricot

How to install:

1. Put all files to some folder that is rendered by the web-server ( for example under document root )
For example, if document root is set to "/var/www/", then files would be at the /var/www/supermarket folder
and would be accessible from http://localhost/supermarket

2. Register and get API key at http://supermarketapi.com

3. Edit config.rb file and add your API key

Done!
